document_title: What is dense breast tissue? Causes, diagnosis, significance and risks
subsection_content:
Dense breast tissue is detected on a mammogram. This is a normal and common finding, especially in young menstruating women.
Breast tissue includes milk glands, milk ducts, connective tissue, and fatty tissue. On mammograms, women with dense breasts have more connective tissue than fatty tissue.
On a mammogram, breast tissue is not dense, dark and transparent. Dense breast tissue appears as a solid white area on a mammogram, making it difficult to detect lesions on the breast.
